    "comment": "Rationale: Pre-embedding immunoelectron microscopy (EM) using a rabbit polyclonal anti-CAPS-2 antibody (anti-a1803/CAPS2 amino acids 18-89) generated in the study. No CAPS-2 KO were used to test antibody specificity for immuno-EM.\n\n31/5/2017 Pim\n- The included immuno-EM pictures show much more detailed location on predantly non-specified presynaptic vesicular structures which are not SVs (for which SynGO has no term) but also on the presynaptic plasma membrane and in the dendritic spine. Since the majority of the protein is in the presynapse and the authors fail to address the nature of the presynaptic vesicle I agree to the term \"presynapse\".. Experimental description: M&M: For electron microscopy of paraformaldehyde-fixed sections, wild-type and CAPS2-/- mice (P15 and P84) were deeply anesthetized with ether and perfused for 15 min with freshly prepared 2% glutaraldehyde and 2% PFA in 0.1 m PB.",
